<paragraph blockId="36.[168,778,581,1067]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,581,605]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity box="[656,778,581,605]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="30.0">30–80 cm</quantity>
height, ramified on the upper nodes. Leaf-blades linear, 3.5–30.0 cm long, 
<quantity box="[364,497,649,673]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.05">0.05–0.2 cm</quantity>
wide, glabrous, with marginal trichomes, ligulate. It is identified by its branched apical inflorescence, 
<quantity box="[398,481,718,742]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6 cm</quantity>
long, pedicel covered with hairs and sessile spikelets with 
<quantity box="[506,619,753,777]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="543" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14 mm</quantity>
awn.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="543" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[168,778,581,1067]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,280,792,816]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Remarks.</emphasis>
Occurs scarcely on the native grassland over shallow soils. Considered Endangered in 
<collectingRegion box="[610,774,827,851]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,357,866,890]" pageId="36" pageNumber="543">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, Northeast (BA state), South and Southeast (except ES state) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
